Elements of the Lie algebra
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
We will consider only the 
\begin_inset Formula $SU\left(2\right)$
\end_inset

 subgroup of 
\begin_inset Formula $U\left(2\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

When it occurs in its role as double cover of the rotational group, the
 quantum system is said to carry “spin”, in particular “spin 
\begin_inset Formula $1/2$
\end_inset

” for the two dimensional irreducible representation.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Elements of the Lie algebra 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X_{j}=-i\frac{\sigma_{j}}{2},
\]

\end_inset

with commutation relations 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[X_{1},X_{2}\right]=X_{3},\hspace{1em}\left[X_{2},X_{3}\right]=X_{1},\left[X_{3},X_{1}\right]=X_{2}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
