\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The unit sphere 
\begin_inset Formula $S^{2}\subset\mathbb{R}^{3}$
\end_inset

 can be mapped to operators by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{x}\rightarrow\sigma\cdot\mathbf{x},
\]

\end_inset

and for each point 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}\in S^{2}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\cdot\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 has eigenvalues 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm1$
\end_inset

.
 Eigenvectors with eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $+1$
\end_inset

 are solutions to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma\cdot\mathbf{x}\left|\psi\right\rangle =\left|\psi\right\rangle .
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
