\begin_layout Itemize
One can characterize the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}\subset\mathcal{H}$
\end_inset

 corresponding to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}\in S^{2}$
\end_inset

 as the solutions to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{S}\cdot\mathbf{x}\left|\psi\right\rangle =\frac{1}{2}\left|\psi\right\rangle ,
\]

\end_inset

thus, the North pole of the sphere is a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

spin-up
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state and the South pole is a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

